# Onboarding System

Onboarding is the first learning experience in LexMastery.

It is not a form.

It is a guided personalization system.

---

# Product Vision

Onboarding exists to:

- Understand user intent
- Personalize learning paths
- Reduce cognitive overload
- Increase retention
- Improve learning outcomes

Every question must improve system intelligence.

---

# Onboarding Philosophy

Onboarding should feel:

- Short
- Human
- Intelligent
- Adaptive
- Non-intrusive

Never overwhelm users with too many questions at once.

---

# Onboarding Flow

1. Welcome Screen
2. Account Setup (or Login Redirect)
3. Jurisdiction Selection
4. Legal Stage Selection
5. Learning Goal Selection
6. Study Time Availability
7. Preferred Learning Style
8. AI Personalization Setup
9. Notification Preferences
10. Summary & Confirmation
11. Redirect to Dashboard

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

OnboardingController (Riverpod)

↓

OnboardingState

↓

OnboardingRepository

↓

API / Local Storage

---

# State Management

Use Riverpod only.

OnboardingState types:

- NotStarted
- InProgress
- StepLoading
- StepCompleted
- Completed
- Error

Never use boolean flags for step tracking.

---

# Step Model

Each step must define:

- id
- title
- description
- input type
- validation rules
- analytics key

---

# Navigation Rules

Onboarding uses stack navigation only.

No bottom navigation during onboarding.

Back navigation is allowed but controlled.

User must not skip required steps.

---

# Data Collection Rules

Collect only what improves:

- Personalization
- Learning path generation
- AI tutor configuration

Do not collect irrelevant data.

---

# Personalization Engine Inputs

- Jurisdiction
- Exam type
- Experience level
- Study time
- Learning preference

---

# API Contracts

POST /onboarding/start

POST /onboarding/step

POST /onboarding/complete

GET /onboarding/status

---

# Offline Behaviour

Onboarding requires connectivity.

If offline:

- Show offline screen
- Block progression
- Allow retry

---

# Analytics Events

onboarding_start

onboarding_step_view

onboarding_step_complete

onboarding_abandon

onboarding_complete

---

# UX Rules

Each step must:

- Have a single focus
- Avoid multi-question screens
- Provide clear progress indicator
- Show estimated time remaining

---

# Validation Rules

Validation must occur:

- On input change (light validation)
- On step submission (strict validation)

Never allow invalid progression.

---

# Error Handling

Errors must:

- Explain clearly
- Provide recovery action
- Allow retry without data loss

---

# Accessibility

All onboarding screens must:

- Support screen readers
- Have clear focus order
- Support dynamic text size
- Avoid time pressure interactions

---

# Performance

Each step should load in <200ms after transition.

Avoid heavy computations in UI layer.

---

# AI Integration

Onboarding feeds AI personalization engine:

- Study recommendations
- Difficulty scaling
- Content prioritization

---

# Security Rules

Do not store onboarding data permanently until completion.

Temporary cache only.

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

OnboardingController

Step validation logic

State transitions

Widget Tests:

Each onboarding step

Navigation flow

Progress indicator

Integration Tests:

Full onboarding flow

Offline rejection flow

Abandon and resume flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating onboarding features:

- Always use step-based architecture
- Always implement OnboardingController
- Always include analytics events
- Always include validation logic
- Always include accessibility support
- Never merge multiple steps into one screen